function_call.name: get_risks
function_call.arguments: {"risks":[{"Description":"Unreliable early stage estimated number of infected humans due to unknown virus characteristics and rapid interventions.","Impact":"Inaccurate depiction of early trend of infected humans, leading to misinformation and underestimation of the spread.","Mitigation":"Increase testing capacity and improve data collection methods to obtain more accurate early stage estimates.","Technologies":"Improved testing methods and data collection technologies.","People":"Public health officials, researchers, and policymakers.","Owner":"Government health agencies and research institutions."},{"Description":"Differences in patterns of movement of crowds and levels of economic development make it difficult to clarify which country's data are most appropriate for simulating the trend of COVID-19.","Impact":"Challenges in accurately simulating the free infected trend of COVID-19, leading to ambiguity in understanding the spread of the virus.","Mitigation":"Develop standardized simulation models that account for global variations in movement patterns and economic development.","Technologies":"Data analytics and modeling software.","People":"Epidemiologists, data scientists, and public health researchers.","Owner":"International health organizations and research institutions."},{"Description":"Use of genetic algorithm to estimate parameters for dynamic model of COVID-19 spread.","Impact":"Reliability and accuracy of parameter estimation may be influenced by the complexity of the virus and its spread dynamics.","Mitigation":"Validate genetic algorithm results with multiple modeling approaches and real-world data to ensure accuracy.","Technologies":"Model validation tools and data comparison algorithms.","People":"Epidemiologists, mathematicians, and data scientists.","Owner":"Research institutions and academic organizations."}]}
